 <p><p><center><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~shay01/cerkin.gif"</center>
</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ucerkin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cerkin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.infinitusvindicat.com/memberpics/iv-logo60x60.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/8/02 8:25:07 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/umorkenlar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morkenlar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Councilman</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/9/02 8:31:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DWI</span><hr size=1> I think part of the issue with that is that we have no standard &quot;you are an adult now&quot; age for kids to follow.  People consider them adults when they graduate high school or college, depending.<br>
<br>
You can get a job at 16 . . . vote, get drafted, buy rifles, and smoke at 18, drink and buy handguns at 21 .. . . why don't these numbers match up? <p></br>

<img src=http://home.attbi.com/~shay01/morksiggy.gif
>


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/umaddiefaye.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maddie Faye</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/10/02 1:48:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fallenalliance.org/screenshots/downwpst.gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DWI</span><hr size=1> I know in my state, you can not buy a hand gun at 18.  You can buy a rifle, or shotgun, but not a handgun.  You may buy a handgun at 21.<br>
<br>
We should just raise the bar.  Right to Vote, drive, drink is all at 21.  <br>
<br>
Draft is still 18 IMHO though, it's like this.  You don't have to be responsible to be in the military.<br>
<br>
I think you should be allowed to enlist at 14; with parent permission or signed off by a judge.  There are some people simply too stupid for school. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=18533>Sister Maddie Faye</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/umorkenlar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morkenlar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Councilman</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/10/02 2:50:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DWI</span><hr size=1> Sorry, Maddie, I have to disagree there.  If you have the duty to get drafted for the protection of society, then you should have a say in how society is run.  voting and draft age should ALWAYS be the same. <p></br>

<img src=http://home.attbi.com/~shay01/morksiggy.gif
>


</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/usapiens1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sapiens1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/12/02 11:09:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DWI</span><hr size=1> I believe we should have  compulsory military service.<br>
<br>
But since we don't...<br>
<br>
I think IF you joint he military you should get all the benefits of being 21.. If not.. you should have to wait till 21...<br>
<br>
Voting, drinking, gun ownership.. etc.. all legal at 21...  If you join military you get those rights right away... you get a dishonorable discharge... loose them again till 25.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/utaxii2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taxii2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/13/02 7:38:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DWI</span><hr size=1> well lets see here Drunk Driving My brother had a ex girlfrend die and her little brother  die because of one about 4 years ago.  <br>
<br>
    A co worker of mine  who is very lucky today  ran off the road hit a fence  crashed into some kind of wall because he was drinking and driving about a month ago.   <br>
<br>
    Another Co Worker of mine just last week lost her best friend to a 19 year old Drunk Driver and her best friends wife will most likely be unable to walk for the rest of her life. Also there 2 kids that were in the back seat were ok but will now live with out there father and there mother basically unable to walk for the rest of her life.<br>
<br>
<br>
so I say screw Drunk Drivers.<br>
<br>
You want to Drink and Drive then all I say is don't hit me because if I'm still alive they wont be. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/uhernelyonsbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Herne Lyonsbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/14/02 6:01:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DWI</span><hr size=1> So in other words sapiens you want to do away with the draft(sorry the selective service) since that person that is drafted into the military did not volunteer to go in? <p>Herne Lyonsbane (retired)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/ummmbaekin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mmmBaekin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/17/02 1:39:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DWI</span><hr size=1> Personally I think all traffic laws should be much more strict.  Automobile wrecks are the number one cause of death because everyone and their mother is driving.  Spend one year in florida, and tell me how many of those people shouldn't be driving.  <br>
<br>
You should have to take a rigorous drivers test to get your license, and retake the full test every 5 years, until age or medical condition requires more frequent testing.  Fewer people on the roads, who are all decent drivers means we can raise speed limits, improve traffic flow, and basically stop catering to the lowest common denominator.<br>
<br>
People have forgotten that driving is a privalege and not a right.  DWI - one strike and you lose your license for life.  i make small considerations for fender benders and speeding cause face it, all of us have days when we make a stupid mistake.  but major screw-ups, drunk driving, excessive speeding - you should be taken off the road for good.<br>
<br>
I lost the same friend herne did - got hit at a red light while he was sitting on his motorcycle.  driver of the pickup was going 40, never saw him sitting there, not to mention the red light.<br>
<br>
Baekin <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showPrevMessage?topicID=39.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showNextMessage?topicID=39.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=21><img src=http://www.infinitusvindicat.com/images/f_addreply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.emailToFriend?topicID=39.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.threadControl?topicID=39.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=39.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/finfinitusvindicatfrm9.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=39.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub79.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="infinitusvindicatfrm1">The Commons<option value="infinitusvindicatfrm3">Guild Store<option value="infinitusvindicatfrm9">OT Discussions and Debates<option value="infinitusvindicatfrm5">Screenshots<option value="infinitusvindicatfrm2">The Inner Sanct